A NullPointerException occurs when you try to use an object reference that is null. Common fixes:

1. **Check for null before calling methods or accessing fields.**
   ```java
   String str = null;
   if (str != null) {
       System.out.println(str.length());
   }
   ```

2. **Initialize variables properly.**
   ```java
   String str = ""; // instead of null
   ```

3. **Use `Optional` to avoid null checks.**
   ```java
   Optional<String> opt = Optional.ofNullable(getString());
   opt.ifPresent(s -> System.out.println(s.length()));
   ```

4. **Ensure array/collection elements are not null before access.**
   ```java
   String[] arr = new String[5];
   arr[0] = "hello";
   if (arr[0] != null) {
       System.out.println(arr[0].length());
   }
   ```

5. **Use `Objects.requireNonNull()` to fail fast.**
   ```java
   public void process(String input) {
       Objects.requireNonNull(input, "input must not be null");
       // safe to use input
   }
   ```

6. **Check return values from methods that may return null.**
   ```java
   String result = someMethod();
   if (result != null) {
       // use result
   }
   ```

Always identify the exact line causing the NPE and trace the null reference back to its source.

